    <div class="calc-layout">
      <div class="calc-main">
        <h1>📅 Days Between Dates Calculator</h1>
        <p class="calc-intro">Calculate the exact number of days, weeks and months between any two dates instantly.</p>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="row-2">
            <div>
              <label>Start date</label>
              <input type="date" id="df-inicio" oninput="calcDias()" style="width:100%;padding:0.65rem 0.9rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;font-size:1rem;background:var(--bg);margin-bottom:1rem">
            </div>
            <div>
              <label>End date</label>
              <input type="date" id="df-fin" oninput="calcDias()" style="width:100%;padding:0.65rem 0.9rem;border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:8px;font-size:1rem;background:var(--bg);margin-bottom:1rem">
            </div>
          </div>
          <label>Count only working days?</label>
          <select id="df-laborables" onchange="calcDias()">
            <option value="no">No, count all days</option>
            <option value="si">Yes, working days only (Mon–Fri)</option>
          </select>
          <div class="result-box" id="df-res">Enter the two dates</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="calc-sidebar">
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h2>What is this calculator for?</h2>
          <p>This date calculator computes the exact difference between two dates in days, weeks and months. It is useful for counting down to an event, calculating how long a project has been running, or finding the number of working days between two dates.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card sidebar-card">
          <h3>Frequently asked questions</h3>
          <details>
            <summary>Does it account for leap years?</summary>
